<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://score-theory.org/agora#"
     xml:base="http://score-theory.org/agora"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:core="http://score-theory.org/core#">

    <!-- AGORA: constitutional & institutional health — the third SCORE implementation,
         and the first Sigma-actor-level peer.
         A refinement P ⊆ S (see obsidian/SCORE/methodology/RefinementArchitecture.md).
         Q1–Q4 analysis: obsidian/SCORE/emergence/applications/AGORA.md.
         Conformance: core ⊕ agora must be consistent under HermiT (score_reason.py). -->
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora">
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core"/>
        <rdfs:comment>AGORA implementation ontology — constitutional and institutional health (branches of government, courts, electoral machinery as the subject). The first Sigma-actor-level peer: it SELECTs the core:SigmaActor spine unchanged and SPECIALIZEs four slots for the domain. AGORA SELECTs the core:SigmaInterventionClass taxonomy (InstitutionalDesign / InterSigmaCoupling / FoundingConditionIntervention / CollectiveManifoldShift) without subclassing — just as POLARIS SELECTs the A-actor CreateRhythm/Edge/Node operators. That taxonomy was Q3-PROMOTED into core on the AGORA n ETHOS intersection (the gap ETHOS pre-registered).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>Refinement conformance verified: core ⊕ agora consistent, no unsatisfiable classes (HermiT via owlready2, 2026-06-04). Reproduce: scripts/score_reason.py.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>


    <!-- ── Fitness-criterion slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:FitnessCriterion) ──
         The SECOND filler of the slot ETHOS's Q3 promotion created — validates that promotion. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#ManifoldCompatibility -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#ManifoldCompatibility">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#FitnessCriterion"/>
        <rdfs:label>Manifold compatibility</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>AGORA NS fitness criterion: the degree to which the institutional maintaining community's manifold positions remain aligned with the constitutional B3 role templates. The central failure mode is role/manifold mismatch at high-centrality nodes (see HighCentralityDisruption.md). The second filler of core:FitnessCriterion after ethos:FloridiInformationHealth, confirming the slot generalizes. Theory: ManifoldCompatibilityDesign.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ── Measurement-model slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:MeasurementModel) ── -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#InstitutionalHealthScore -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#InstitutionalHealthScore">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#MeasurementModel"/>
        <rdfs:label>Institutional health score</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>AGORA attractor-health measurement model — the role-level SEWI analog (fills core:MeasurementModel; NOT a core:SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator — a structural/rate composite, not a spectral trace processor; see SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator.md). Composite of uncorrected-norm-violation rate, maintaining-community density at key institutional nodes, manifold-alignment distribution across branches, speed-asymmetry ratio (violations generated vs. corrected), and tri-branch capture index. Domain-specific refinement; no InstitutionalHealthScore in core.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ── HOA-analog slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:HumanCommunity) ── -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#InstitutionalMaintainingCommunity -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#InstitutionalMaintainingCommunity">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#HumanCommunity"/>
        <rdfs:label>Institutional maintaining community</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>AGORA HOA analog: the network of role-occupying A-actors who actively incorporate the constitutional B3 — the apparatus that constitutes legitimate governance, not the electorate. Parallel to polaris:GeographicCommunity and ethos:EpistemicCommunity, but the community that MAINTAINS an institution rather than the one being measured. Its erosion (maintaining-community replacement) is the Mechanism-1 attack in HighCentralityDisruption.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ── Sigma-actor specialization (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:SigmaActor) ── -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#ConstitutionalSigmaActor -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#ConstitutionalSigmaActor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor"/>
        <rdfs:label>Constitutional Sigma-actor</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A branch of government, court, or electoral body as a Sigma-actor whose function is to sustain constitutional B3 against decay or capture. Inherits the core Sigma-actor formation/maintenance axioms (formedBy CoInscriptionEvent, maintainedBy HumanCommunity, inscribesTo TelosBearingContent, hasReflexiveDepth SufficientDepth). The first domain SELECT+SPECIALIZE of the core:SigmaActor spine. See HighCentralityDisruption.md (Level-0).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ════════════════ Phase C (2026-06-18): collective-manifold-update under captured correction ════════════════
         AGORA half of the AGORA n ATLAS intersection that licensed the sixth on-demand Q3 promotion
         (core:CollectiveManifoldUpdate). ATLAS's atlas:CoverageModulatedReception is the second peer.
         The dynamical result — captured-only correction cannot drive role/manifold mismatch to zero
         without an IndependentNode — is DL-inexpressible: Lean captured_correction_needs_independent_node
         (formal/Formal/Score/Agora.lean See AGORA-CollectiveManifoldUpdate.md. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#correctedBy -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#correctedBy">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/agora#CapturedCorrectionUpdate"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/agora#CorrectingNode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The node through which institutional correction is routed. Whether it is an IndependentNode or a CapturedNode determines whether role/manifold mismatch can be driven to zero.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#CapturedCorrectionUpdate -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#CapturedCorrectionUpdate">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#CollectiveManifoldUpdate"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/agora#correctedBy"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/agora#CorrectingNode"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label>Captured-correction update</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>AGORA's specialization of the promoted core:CollectiveManifoldUpdate: the update of an institution's collective manifold when correction must run without the violating actor's cooperation. The AGORA half of the AGORA n ATLAS intersection that licensed the promotion. That captured-only correction cannot drive mismatch to zero without an IndependentNode is the entrenchment result — DL-inexpressible, in Lean captured_correction_needs_independent_node (formal/Formal/Score/Agora.lean See AGORA-CollectiveManifoldUpdate.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#CorrectingNode -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#CorrectingNode">
        <rdfs:comment>A node through which institutional correction is routed. Two disjoint kinds (below): an IndependentNode (own-mismatch ~ 0, enabling mismatch -> 0) and a CapturedNode (own-mismatch above a positive floor).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#IndependentNode -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#IndependentNode">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/agora#CorrectingNode"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/agora#CapturedNode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A correcting node not itself drifted: routing correction through it can drive role/manifold mismatch to zero. Structural entrenchment ahead of capture is exactly guaranteeing such a node exists.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#CapturedNode -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#CapturedNode">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/agora#CorrectingNode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A correcting node itself drifted above a positive mismatch floor: correction routed through it cannot reduce mismatch below that floor. When all available nodes are captured, the capture is irreversible (generational, for judicial capture).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ── Doctrinal-region + composition fillers (Q2 SPECIALIZE of the promoted
         core:DoctrinalRegion / core:doctrinallyComposesFrom; eighth-promotion slot, 2026-06-21).
         The most LITERAL down-closure in the family: under stare decisis a holding legally
         requires its precedential / constitutional substrate. Region-bearer:
         agora:InstitutionalMaintainingCommunity. Lean formal/Formal/Score/Agora.lean (agoraNetwork). -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#citesAuthority -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#citesAuthority">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#doctrinallyComposesFrom"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Legal-authority citation among B3 legal inscriptions: `y citesAuthority x` means ruling/doctrine y is grounded in substrate x (constitution, statute, precedent). The AGORA instance of core:doctrinallyComposesFrom; under stare decisis this is requirement, not mere reference, so a DoctrinalCorpus is strongly down-closed.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/agora#DoctrinalCorpus -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/agora#DoctrinalCorpus">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#DoctrinalRegion"/>
        <rdfs:label>Doctrinal corpus</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The body of constitutional/legal doctrine an agora:InstitutionalMaintainingCommunity holds and maintains: the graded down-set of the citesAuthority DAG. The AGORA filler of core:DoctrinalRegion — the most literal down-closure in the family (a holding requires its precedential substrate). Lean: formal/Formal/Score/Agora.lean (agoraCorpus, agoraCorpus_isRegion). See AGORA.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

</rdf:RDF>
